This is a variable:

myage = 0

The variable is variable therrfore ou can modify this data

EVERY TIME you declare a new variable you have to give an initial value.

define multiple variable:

myage, myname = 20, 'Paul'

equivalnet to:

myage = 20
myname = 'Paul'

A VARIABLE CANNOT HAVE A NUMBER AS FIRST CHARACTER
there are also some reserverd words that you cannot use as a variable name

VARIABLE NAMES ARE CASE SENSITIVE

It is usually used 'camel case' that is the practice of writing compound words with mixed casing
or it is used the underscore to separate a vairable name like:

this_is_my_variable
